									<h3>Key Considerations in Selecting Fabrics</h3>
									<p>
										Consider these points when selecting fabrics for digital textile printing on fabric:
										Ink Compatibility: Different inks (pigment-, dye- and reactive inks) work better with certain
										fabrics than others.
										Texture and Weave: Fabrics that feature tight weaves typically produce sharper prints.
										Absorbency: Fabrics that absorb ink well prevent bleeding and produce vibrant colors, providing
										vibrant results.
										End Use: When selecting fabric for clothing, upholstery or banners, its purpose has an impactful
										bearing.
										Durability: For prints designed to be worn and washed frequently, fabric durability is of utmost
										importance.
